<!-- ── Problems ── -->
<section class="problems-bg">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="margin-bottom:48px">
      <div class="section-tag">why jamjet</div>
      <h2>Production agents have<br/>unsolved problems.</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--text-muted);margin-top:12px;font-size:1.05rem;">Every team building real agent systems hits the same walls.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">RELIABILITY</div>
        <h3>Agents crash and lose everything</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">In-process orchestration libraries vanish on restart. No state, no recovery, no trace of what happened.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ durable graph execution with event sourcing</div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">INTEROP</div>
        <h3>Agents are locked in silos</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">LangChain agents can't talk to AutoGen. CrewAI can't delegate to your partner's system. Everyone's isolated.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ native MCP + A2A protocols</div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">OBSERVABILITY</div>
        <h3>You can't see what's happening</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">No cost attribution per node, no event timeline, no structured telemetry. Debugging is guesswork.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ OTel GenAI traces + checkpoint replay</div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">SAFETY</div>
        <h3>Autonomous agents run forever</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">No standard way to enforce token budgets, cost limits, or iteration caps. Agents burn money until you kill them.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ compile-time autonomy constraints</div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">PROCESS</div>
        <h3>Human approval is bolted on</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">Pausing for a human decision requires polling loops, external webhooks, fragile stateful callbacks.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ human-in-the-loop as a native node type</div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">PERFORMANCE</div>
        <h3>Python orchestration doesn't scale</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">GIL contention, asyncio overhead, per-call Python tax. Your orchestrator becomes the bottleneck.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ Rust async scheduler, microsecond overhead</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="sep"/>

<!-- ── Features ── -->
<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div style="margin-bottom:48px">
      <div class="section-tag">features</div>
      <h2>Everything production demands.<br/>Nothing extra.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="features-grid">
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">durability</div>
        <h3>Durable Graph Execution</h3>
        <p>Every step checkpointed. Crash the process, restart it — execution resumes exactly where it stopped. Event sourcing + periodic snapshots.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">protocols</div>
        <h3>Native MCP + A2A</h3>
        <p>MCP client + server. A2A client + server. Connect to any tool server, expose your tools, delegate to or serve external agents — in your workflow YAML.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">humans</div>
        <h3>Human-in-the-Loop</h3>
        <p>Pause any workflow for human approval. Suspends durably — restarts and crashes don't lose the state. Resume via API, CLI, or webhook.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">identity</div>
        <h3>Agent-Native Identity</h3>
        <p>Every agent has a URI and an Agent Card describing capabilities. Managed lifecycle, discoverable via A2A, composable across orgs and frameworks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">observability</div>
        <h3>Full Observability</h3>
        <p>OTel GenAI traces. Per-node token and cost attribution. Structured event timeline. Checkpoint replay for any execution. Know exactly what happened.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">typing</div>
        <h3>Typed Schemas Everywhere</h3>
        <p>Pydantic, TypedDict, or JSON Schema for all inputs and outputs. No stringly-typed state. Schema violations fail fast at validation time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">autonomy</div>
        <h3>Configurable Autonomy Limits</h3>
        <p>Token budgets, cost caps, iteration limits, tool allowlists, approval requirements per agent — enforced at runtime with clear events and escalation paths.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">evaluation</div>
        <h3>Native Eval Harness</h3>
        <p>LLM-judge, assertion, latency, and cost scorers as first-class workflow nodes. Run <kbd>jamjet eval run --dataset qa.jsonl --fail-below 80</kbd> in CI.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">performance</div>
        <h3>Rust Core, Python Authoring</h3>
        <p>Scheduler, state machine, and worker pool are Rust + Tokio. Workflows and tools are Python. Systems performance, developer ergonomics.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="sep"/>

<!-- ── Code examples ── -->
<section style="background: var(--bg-2)">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="margin-bottom:48px">
      <div class="section-tag">authoring</div>
      <h2>Write workflows your way.</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--text-muted); margin-top:12px; font-size:1.05rem;">YAML for clarity, Python for flexibility. Both compile to the same durable runtime graph.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="code-wrap">
      <div class="tab-strip">
        <button class="tab active" data-tab-target="yaml">workflow.yaml</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab-target="python">python sdk</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab-target="agent">agent.yaml</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab-target="mcp">mcp tools</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab-target="eval">eval node</button>
      </div>

      <div id="pane-yaml" class="tab-pane active">
        <pre class="code"><span class="cmt"># workflow.yaml — RAG pipeline with human approval</span>
<span class="kw">workflow:</span>
  id: rag-with-approval
  version: <span class="str">0.1.0</span>
  state_schema: schemas.ResearchState
  start: fetch_context

<span class="kw">nodes:</span>
  <span class="dec">fetch_context:</span>
    type: mcp_tool
    server: vector_db
    tool: similarity_search
    input:
      query: <span class="str">"&#123;&#123; state.question &#125;&#125;"</span>
    output_schema: schemas.Chunks
    next: synthesize

  <span class="dec">synthesize:</span>
    type: model
    model: claude-sonnet-4-6
    prompt: prompts/synthesize.md
    output_schema: schemas.Answer
    next: approve

  <span class="dec">approve:</span>
    type: human_approval          <span class="cmt"># durable — survives restarts</span>
    description: <span class="str">"Review answer before delivery"</span>
    timeout_secs: <span class="str">86400</span>           <span class="cmt"># 24h window</span>
    next: deliver

  <span class="dec">deliver:</span>
    type: tool
    tool_ref: tools.send_response
    input:
      answer: <span class="str">"&#123;&#123; state.answer &#125;&#125;"</span></pre>
      </div>

      <div id="pane-python" class="tab-pane">
        <pre class="code"><span class="kw">from</span> jamjet <span class="kw">import</span> Workflow, tool
<span class="kw">from</span> pydantic <span class="kw">import</span> BaseModel

<span class="cls">class</span> <span class="typ">ResearchState</span>(BaseModel):
    question: <span class="typ">str</span>
    answer:   <span class="typ">str | None</span> = None

workflow = Workflow(<span class="str">"research"</span>)

<span class="dec">@tool</span>
<span class="kw">async def</span> <span class="fn">web_search</span>(query: <span class="typ">str</span>) -> <span class="typ">list[str]</span>:
    <span class="str">"""Fetch search results for query."""</span>
    ...

<span class="dec">@workflow.step</span>
<span class="kw">async def</span> <span class="fn">search</span>(state: ResearchState) -> ResearchState:
    results = <span class="kw">await</span> web_search(query=state.question)
    <span class="kw">return</span> state.model_copy(update=&#123;<span class="str">"results"</span>: results&#125;)

<span class="dec">@workflow.step</span>
<span class="kw">async def</span> <span class="fn">synthesize</span>(state: ResearchState) -> ResearchState:
    <span class="cmt"># JamJet calls the model; result is checkpointed</span>
    ...

<span class="dec">@workflow.human_approval</span>(timeout_hours=<span class="str">24</span>)
<span class="kw">async def</span> <span class="fn">approve</span>(state: ResearchState) -> ResearchState:
    <span class="cmt"># Suspends durably until human approves via CLI or API</span>
    ...</pre>
      </div>

      <div id="pane-agent" class="tab-pane">
        <pre class="code"><span class="cmt"># agent.yaml — ReAct agent with enforced limits</span>
<span class="kw">agent:</span>
  id: research-analyst
  name: Research Analyst
  model: claude-sonnet-4-6
  strategy: react               <span class="cmt"># react | plan_and_execute | critic</span>

  <span class="kw">tools:</span>
    - tool_ref: tools.web_search
    - tool_ref: tools.read_url
    - tool_ref: tools.code_exec

  <span class="kw">mcp:</span>
    servers:
      arxiv:
        transport: http_sse
        url: https://mcp.arxiv.org/v1

  <span class="kw">limits:</span>                        <span class="cmt"># enforced at runtime</span>
    max_iterations: <span class="str">10</span>
    token_budget: <span class="str">50000</span>
    cost_budget_usd: <span class="str">0.50</span>
    time_budget_secs: <span class="str">300</span>
    on_limit_exceeded: escalate  <span class="cmt"># escalate | halt | log_and_continue</span>

  autonomy: bounded_autonomous   <span class="cmt"># guided | bounded_autonomous | fully_autonomous</span></pre>
      </div>

      <div id="pane-mcp" class="tab-pane">
        <pre class="code"><span class="cmt"># Use any MCP server as a workflow node</span>
<span class="kw">mcp_servers:</span>
  github:
    transport: http_sse
    url: https://mcp.github.com/v1
    auth:
      type: bearer
      token_env: GITHUB_TOKEN

  postgres:
    transport: stdio
    command: npx -y @modelcontextprotocol/server-postgres
    args: [<span class="str">"postgresql://localhost/mydb"</span>]

<span class="kw">nodes:</span>
  search_code:
    type: mcp_tool
    server: github              <span class="cmt"># ↑ references mcp_servers.github</span>
    tool: search_code
    input:
      query: <span class="str">"&#123;&#123; state.query &#125;&#125;"</span>
    next: store_result

  store_result:
    type: mcp_tool
    server: postgres
    tool: insert_row
    input:
      table: <span class="str">"analysis_results"</span>
      data:  <span class="str">"&#123;&#123; state.result &#125;&#125;"</span></pre>
      </div>

      <div id="pane-eval" class="tab-pane">
        <pre class="code"><span class="cmt"># eval node in workflow — LLM-judge + assertions + cost gate</span>
<span class="kw">nodes:</span>
  generate:
    type: model
    model: claude-sonnet-4-6
    prompt: prompts/answer.md
    next: <span class="dec">evaluate</span>

  <span class="dec">evaluate:</span>
    type: eval
    <span class="kw">scorers:</span>
      - type: llm_judge
        model: claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
        rubric: <span class="str">"Rate factual accuracy 1–5"</span>
        min_score: <span class="str">3</span>
      - type: assertion
        checks:
          - <span class="str">"'answer' in output"</span>
          - <span class="str">"len(output['answer']) > 20"</span>
      - type: cost
        threshold_usd: <span class="str">0.05</span>
    on_fail: retry_with_feedback
    max_retries: <span class="str">2</span>
    next: deliver

<span class="cmt"># Or from the CLI for batch CI scoring:</span>
<span class="cmt"># jamjet eval run qa.jsonl --workflow rag \</span>
<span class="cmt">#   --rubric "Rate accuracy 1-5" --fail-below 80</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

